-- Religare Enterprises, Shipping Corp., Oil & Natural: India Equity Preview
-- V. Ramakrishnan
-- 2010-04-27T01:51:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-27/religare-enterprises-shipping-corp-oil-natural-india-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
unusual price changes in India trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the last close.  
 The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or Sensex, rose
0.3 percent to 17,745.28. The S&P CNX Nifty Index on the
National Stock Exchange advanced 0.4 percent to 5,322.45. The
BSE 200 Index increased 0.4 percent to 2,242.25. SGX S&P CNX
Nifty Index futures for April delivery retreated 0.2 percent to
5,310.5 at 9:39 a.m. in Singapore today.  
 Oil & Natural Gas Corp. (ONGC IN): The oil and gas
exploration company made three discoveries in April, it said in
a statement yesterday. The shares were little changed at
1,017.75 rupees.  
 Religare Enterprises Ltd. (RELG IN): The financial services
company posted profit of 317.2 million rupees in the quarter
ended March, compared with a loss of 652.7 million rupees in the
same period a year earlier, it said in a statement yesterday.
The shares lost 2 percent to 430.5 rupees.  
 Shipping Corp. of India Ltd. (SCI IN): The state-owned
company plans to spend about $1 billion in the financial year
that began April 1 to buy vessels, Chairman S. Hajara said
yesterday. The shares advanced 0.6 percent to 160.3 rupees.  
 Sterlite Industries (India) Ltd. (STLT IN): The metals
company will start work on doubling its copper smelter capacity,
Navin Agarwal, executive vice president, said in a conference
call yesterday. The shares advanced 6 percent to 842.6 rupees.  
